    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legalise adult adoption",
        "additional_details": "Places legalising adult adoption include:\r\n- Some US States\r\n- Some Provinces in Canada\r\n- Japan\r\n- Germany\r\n \r\nThe age for adoption ends when the individual reaches 18. Due to this being the cut off age, this doesn't give the individual the independence of being classed as an adult and processing their own adoption application. Applications made prior to the age of 18 are subject to the approval of the named parents, except in specific circumstance.\r\n \r\nWe believe this law is extremely detrimental to the mental health of individuals who have experienced abuse at the hand of their parent(s).\r\n",
        "background": "We think it is time for adult adoption to be legalised in the UK.\r\n\r\nWe believe amending this law would offer individuals the opportunity, as a legal adult, to sever connections with absent, abusive, or otherwise unsuitable parents.",
